## Template Corrections Cần Update

Dựa trên phân tích, các điểm trong `the_well_studio_template.md` cần hiệu chỉnh:

### Storyboard Breakdown — Transition Rules

```diff
 [Editing Pattern Rules]
-- 5% Hard cuts — RARE
-- 75% Cross Dissolve (1000-2000ms) — PRIMARY TRANSITION
-- 10% Fade to Black (1500ms)
-- 5% Fade from Black
-- 5% Soft Cut

++ 90% Hard Cut — PRIMARY TRANSITION. Clean, story-driven.
++ 5% Cross Dissolve — ONLY for time passage (season change) or reality→dream
++ 5% Fade to Black — Video ending only
```

### Video Constraint — Slow Motion Addition

```diff
 **Subject Micro-Movement (AI Video - Subtle Only):**
+  **Slow Motion (SIGNATURE)**: ~80% playback speed on atmospheric shots.
+  Apply to: falling leaves, rain particles, fireflies, walking scenes,
+  wool fuzz movement in wind. Creates "magical realism" quality.
+  Approximately 80% of all shots use this subtle slow-motion.
```

### Video Constraint — Walking Direction

```diff
+  **Walking Direction (HARD RULE)**: Characters ALWAYS walk LEFT → RIGHT
+  on screen. This symbolizes forward progress on their spiritual journey.
+  RIGHT → LEFT only if character is "going back" to a mistake/past.
```

### Style Prompt — Diverse Settings

```diff
 **Common scene types:**
+  * Urban environment (needle-felted New York, felt taxi cab, miniature city buildings — used for "lost in the world" metaphor)
+  * Ocean/Beach (resin water, felt sand, shipwreck debris — used for crisis/rescue)
+  * Airplane interior (miniature felt seats, tiny windows — used for life journey/turbulence metaphor)
+  * Cave/Grotto (wool/felt interior, campfire, fireflies — used for Bridge intimacy scenes)
+  * Seasonal landscapes — spring flowers, autumn leaves, winter snow, summer meadow (used for time-passage montage)
```

### Character Extraction — Antagonists

```diff
+  * **Wolves (Antagonist)**: Needle-felted wolf figurines with glowing bead eyes.
+    Dark grey/black wool. Appear in packs of 3-5. Only in "Darkness" sections.
+    RETREAT immediately when Jesus appears. Still look handcrafted/cute-scary,
+    never truly terrifying.
+  * **Storm elements**: Yarn lightning bolts, cotton/wool clouds, felt rain drops.
+    All weather is ALSO needle-felted / textile material.
```

